The Proposal -

Mauje Mangrul, Pimpri Kalaga, Jhombadi, Vatphad, Pimpalgaon Kale, Tembi, Lonadi Ta. Nallah deepening and widening work is proposed including the Causeway Dam at Ner District Yavatmal. The river / rivulet flowing in and around the villages in the catchment area is getting heavy floods every year due to which the river is spreading on both sides causing damage to the shoals on the banks as well as flood water entering the villages on the banks of the river. The river / rivulet erosion has been greatly reduced due to the very slow slope of the river / rivulet as well as the accumulation of silt. This has reduced the discharge capacity of the river / rivulet. Heavy rains have caused extensive damage to the village and agricultural crops, with reports of farm losses in some areas.

Similarly, a causeway has been proposed at Dwarukt so that after the end of the monsoon season, it will be possible to block the water by opening the gate and farmers will be able to use the causeway to go from one end of the drain to the other. This deepening will help meet the objective of water conservation along with flood protection by augmenting the water storage available from the existing dam to replenish it. These works are proposed on an experimental basis. The estimated cost of the work is Rs. 4,97,24, 772 / - and the Government was considering granting administrative sanction for the work.
